21/06/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Korca arrested two officials from the city court on Saturday (June 19th). Arben Hoxha, head of staff in charge of executing criminal sentences and Shkeqim Kajmaku, a councillor at the court, are suspected of corruption. A total of 4,000 euros in their possession was seized as evidence. Investigations are ongoing to reveal details of cases in which they assisted, allegedly in return for bribes. (Shekulli, Start, Top Channel, Ora News - 20/06/10)
